\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Amplification (rhetoric)}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Amplification refers to a literary practice wherein the writer embellishes the sentence by adding more information to it in order to increase its worth and understanding.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 E.g., Original sentence: The thesis paper was difficult. After amplification: The thesis paper was difficult: it required extensive research, data collection, sample surveys, interviews and a lot of fieldwork.}
