\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Asyndeton}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 When sentences do not use conjunctions (e.g., and, or, nor) to separate clauses, but run clauses into one another, usually marking the separation of clauses with punctuation.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 An example is when John F. Kennedy said on January 20, 1961 "...that we shall pay any price, bear any burden, meet any hardship, support any friend, oppose any foe to assure the survival and the success of liberty."}
