\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Dramatic visualization}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Representing an object or character with abundant descriptive detail, or mimetically rendering gestures and dialogue to make a scene more visual or imaginatively present to an audience.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 This technique appears at least as far back as the Arabian Nights.[11]}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Euphuism}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 An artificial, highly elaborate way of writing or speaking. Named from Euphues (1579) the prose romance by John Lyly.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 "Is it not far better to abhor sins by the remembrance of others' faults, than by repentance of thine own follies?" (from Euphues, 1, lecture by the wise Neapolitan)}
