\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Metonymy}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Word or phrase in a figure of speech in which a noun is referenced by something closely associated with it, rather than explicitly by the noun itself. This is not to be confused with synecdoche, in which a part of the whole stands for the thing itself.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Metonomy: The boxer threw in the towel. Synecdoche: She gave her hand in marriage.}
