\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Polysyndeton}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Polysyndeton is the use of several conjunctions in close succession, this provides a sense of exaggeration designed to wear down the audience.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 An example of this is in the first chapter of Great Expectations by Charles Dickens: "A man who had been soaked in water, and smothered in mud, and lamed by stones, and cut by flints, and stung by nettles, and torn by briars; who limped, and shivered, and glared and growled; and whose teeth chattered in his head as he seized me by the chin"}
